## Authentication

{% if use_auth %}
This API uses **{{ auth_strategy | upper }}** authentication.

{% if auth_strategy == "jwt" %}
Include the token in all protected requests:

```http
Authorization: Bearer <your-token>
```

Tokens expire after 24 hours. Use the refresh endpoint to obtain a new token without re-authenticating.
{% elif auth_strategy == "oauth2" %}
Authentication follows the OAuth2 Authorization Code flow. Redirect users to `/api/v1/auth/authorize` to begin the flow. The API will exchange the code for tokens and return a session.
{% elif auth_strategy == "api-key" %}
Include your API key in the request header:

```http
X-API-Key: <your-api-key>
```

API keys are issued per application and should never be exposed in client-side code.
{% endif %}
{% else %}
This API does not require authentication. All endpoints are publicly accessible.
{% endif %}

## Testing

Strategy: **{{ test_strategy }}**

{% if framework == "fastapi" or framework == "django-rest" %}
```bash
# Run all tests
pytest

# Run with coverage
pytest --cov=src --cov-report=term-missing

# Run only unit tests
pytest tests/ -m "not integration"

# Run only integration tests
pytest tests/integration/
```
{% elif framework == "express" %}
```bash
# Run all tests
npm test

# Run with coverage
npm run test:coverage

# Run only unit tests
npm run test:unit

# Run only integration tests
npm run test:integration
```
{% elif framework == "spring-boot" %}
```bash
# Run all tests
./mvnw test

# Run with coverage report
./mvnw test jacoco:report

# Run only unit tests
./mvnw test -Dgroups="unit"

# Run only integration tests
./mvnw test -Dgroups="integration"
```
{% endif %}

{% if test_strategy == "unit-and-integration" %}
- Unit tests cover service logic and data transformations
- Integration tests run against a real {{ database }} instance
- Target: >80% coverage on business logic
{% elif test_strategy == "contract-testing" %}
- Consumer-driven contract tests verify API shape
- Provider tests ensure the API meets consumer expectations
- Integration tests cover database interactions
{% elif test_strategy == "full-pyramid" %}
- Unit tests cover all pure functions and service logic
- Integration tests cover database queries and external service calls
- Contract tests cover API consumer expectations
- Target: >80% unit coverage, >60% integration coverage
{% endif %}

## Configuration

Environment variables are loaded from `.env` (development) or the system environment (production).

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | Database connection string | - |
{% if framework == "fastapi" or framework == "django-rest" %}
| `SECRET_KEY` | Application secret key | - |
| `DEBUG` | Enable debug mode | `false` |
| `ALLOWED_HOSTS` | Comma-separated allowed hosts | `*` |
{% elif framework == "express" %}
| `PORT` | Port to listen on | `3000` |
| `NODE_ENV` | Environment name | `development` |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Secret for signing tokens | - |
{% elif framework == "spring-boot" %}
| `SERVER_PORT` | Port to listen on | `8080` |
| `SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE` | Active Spring profiles | `local` |
{% endif %}
{% if use_auth and auth_strategy == "jwt" %}
| `JWT_SECRET` | Secret for signing JWT tokens | - |
| `JWT_EXPIRY` | Token expiry duration | `24h` |
{% elif use_auth and auth_strategy == "oauth2" %}
| `OAUTH_CLIENT_ID` | OAuth2 client ID | - |
| `OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET` | OAuth2 client secret | - |
| `OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI` | Callback URL after auth | - |
{% endif %}

